### 7.10 ZPE-Music — Symbolic-Score Encoding with Note-Local Expression

**Status:** Active
**Domain:** Deterministic encoding of symbolic musical scores with bounded note-local expression carried as a fiber on the same note event.
**Compass-8 Pattern:** NO — uses a symbolic-score base with note-local expression attached as a typed fiber on the authority-native score note.

**Novel Contributions:**

1. **Score-note base with note-local expression fiber.** A deterministic codec in which a symbolic score note is the base object and bounded note-local expression — attack, release, onset offset, duration offset, and velocity — is carried as a separately-typed fiber on that same note event, including across repeated same-pitch notes. The note-anchored expression-attachment contract, such that expression is not represented as a second performed-note stream and remains structurally bound to the authority-native score note, is the novel contribution. Code: resolved via the Citation Index at the Master Resolver Endpoint (ZPE-Music).

2. **Deterministic same-pitch repeated-note disambiguation.** A codec-level disambiguation surface that maintains note-local expression attachment across repeated same-pitch note events, preserving per-note expression identity rather than collapsing expression onto a pitch-keyed index. The repeated-same-pitch deterministic attachment behaviour, tied to the score-note base and the expression fiber, is the novel contribution. Code: resolved via the Citation Index at the Master Resolver Endpoint (ZPE-Music).

**Honest Limits:** ZPE-Music is a bounded symbolic-score codec with note-local expression attachment. The Licensor makes no claim to audio understanding, waveform encoding, pedal or sustain modelling, or full continuous performance modelling. Expression is restricted to attack, release, onset offset, duration offset, and velocity as typed fiber channels on the score note; it is not a general music-performance or audio-rendering claim.

