### 7.15 ZPE-Taste — Taste Geometry-Seam Reference (Evidenced Negative)

**Status:** EVIDENCED NEGATIVE
**Domain:** Taste-lane evaluation of the full geometry burden on the admissible object, published as a negative reference.
**Compass-8 Pattern:** Not applicable — no positive codec claim is made for this lane under this License.

**Publicly Registered Negative Result:**

Under the full geometry burden on the admissible taste object — with helper leakage and packet-identity laundering removed — metric, topology, manifold, and graph/relational structure all fail. The honest registered result for the bounded taste lane is `not_geometry_bearing`. Packet transport for the bounded object exists at the mechanical level, but no admissible geometry seam survives on the admissible object once the confounds are removed.

**Honest Limits and Negative-Reference Framing:** ZPE-Taste is **Evidenced Negative** and is published as a negative reference, not as a codec product. Nothing in this schedule shall be construed as: (i) an implied or delayed positive codec for taste; (ii) a claim that the lane is "almost there" or will convert to a positive in a subsequent version of this License; (iii) a proof that biological taste coding is impossible in general; or (iv) a basis for a Commercial License on a positive taste product. The Licensor makes no positive codec claim under this License for the taste lane. Any public-facing description, third-party benchmark, marketing material, or downstream integration must preserve the negative-reference framing. Presenting ZPE-Taste as a positive, near-positive, or commercialisable taste codec is outside the Licensor's claim surface and is not authorised under this License.

